@asthehosptuRNs the upside is that I am 5 minutes from home, don't work nights/weekends, love my job, and get to work with kids.
@tx_tine I like my car, and it's almost paid for.  It would be nice to have a new one, but I'd rather spend money on my kids right now.
@asthehosptuRNs I didn't realize how much free time I had while in school.  Now, I work 40-45 hours/week, and don't want to talk to anyone.
@tx_tine a lot of my classmates bought cars after graduation. I'm just thankful to be able to pay my bills, pay back loans, and eat out.
I seriously need to reconnect with the world.  Working all the time is sucking the life out of me.
I hope my nurse friends are doing well; my job in pedi triage is keeping me very busy!
http://t.co/IiKIe0L4 my dear friend is marking five years with neuroblastoma today.
I start my second nursing job tomorrow, and can't wait! I think it will be many times better than the last one.
Since the last two months have been *interesting*, I am publishing the story in a series of blog posts. Don't want to bore everyone at once.
Stethoscopes and Scrubs: The saga of my first nursing job http://t.co/XyLS3Ab
My first nursing job turned out to be nothing like it was promised in the interview, so next Friday is my last day...
After spending eight hours driving around Houston today, I can't cool off. This job is going to kill me!
On my way to see my first patient of the day. It was a looong morning in the office!
@tx_tine I feel the same way! I think it's why I became a teacher.
I left the house at 6:45 this morning. One work day and CPR class later, I'm just getting home. 8 hours until I leave for work again; yay.
@KendraBSN12 I had the same ones, but in white, for school. It's so nice to wear different-colored scrubs, too!

I am really enjoying my job, but wish it came with a helicopter. The 45-mile commute is exhausting!
I must learn to do more housework after work during the week and plan our meals, so I can have some time to relax on the weekend.
I am infinitely thankful that my first week of work is a short one. That hour-long commute is killing me!
It's official; I am a Registered Nurse! Now, someone please hire me...
@sharpcheddar wow! Texas isn't nearly that fast. It takes at least a week to get our license number.
@sharpcheddar I agree completely. I'll pay for the Quick Results on Thursday.
If the Pearson Vue "trick" really works, I passed NCLEX. Not going to rely on that, though. Don't want to be disappointed.
75 questions later, I'm on my way home...
Am I really taking NCLEX this morning? I blinked, and the past two years went by. Eek!
What's the most effective way to study for NCLEX, if a person (ahem, not me) waited to study until a week before the test?
@tx_tine how about a See and Say? Those are cute toys, and kids love animal noises.
One week until I take NCLEX. Eek! Can't wait to put that behind me. Oh, and find a job...
I don't think I'm ever going to find a nursing job; never heard back from last Friday's interview. Maybe I can get work as a PCA.

@EstelleDarling I lived there for a year, and never ran out of things to do.  Of course, I was in school, waitressing, no kids.
I think I've applied for 15 nursing jobs today.  Time to call it a day, and stop ignoring my kids.
Still waiting on GN status, and my ATT. Wonder why it's taking so long?
Looking for a job is exhausting! I have a couple of possibilities; hope I hear from them soon.

Did I really just graduate from nursing school? Wow! Anyone want to hire me?
I rocked that HESI! You may now call me Alana Ansley, Graduate Nurse!!!

Done with lecture for the week. Woohoo!

@EstelleDarling he didn't even get that far with me. Bizarre. Either he's selling something, or he just wants to see his name in print.
